Name

grok - Perl 6 documentation reader

Synopsis

`grok <options>`

    Options:
      -F FILE, --file=FILE     Read documentation from the supplied file


Prior art and inspiration
    1. Perl 5's `perldoc` <http://perldoc.perl.org/perldoc.html>
    
    2. Python's `pydoc` <http://docs.python.org/library/pydoc.html>
    
    3. Ruby's `ri` <http://svn.ruby-lang.org/cgi-bin/viewvc.cgi/trunk/lib/rdoc/>
    
    4. http://svn.pugscode.org/pugs/ext/Perldoc/
    
    5. http://svn.pugscode.org/pugs/examples/perldoc.pl

Warning

Bugs in `Perl6::Perldoc`

Long lines are not wrapped to fit your terminal. Whitespace in paragraphs is
preserved, counter to the spec.

Formatting codes using french quotes (`C«»`) aren't parsed correctly, so they
are rendered verbatim.

